  <static seed="115" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberAdditionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>Each page of a book consists of a header, a footer and the middle part. The header is <m>{{\frac{3}{5}}}</m> inches in height; the footer is <m>{{\frac{3}{10}}}</m> inches in height; and the middle part is <m>{3{\textstyle\frac{3}{5}}}</m> inches in height.</p>
<p>What is the total height of each page in this book? Use mixed number in your answer if needed.</p>
<p>Each page in this book is <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> inches in height.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>4{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We add up the height of the header, middle part and footer to find the total height of a page:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{3}{5}}} + {3{\textstyle\frac{3}{5}}} + {{\frac{3}{10}}}
      \amp =    {{\frac{3}{5}}} + 3 + {{\frac{3}{5}}} + {{\frac{3}{10}}} \\
      \amp =    3 + {{\frac{3}{5}}} + {{\frac{3}{5}}} + {{\frac{3}{10}}} \\
      \amp = 3 + \frac{3\cdot2}{5\cdot2} + \frac{3\cdot2}{5\cdot2} + \frac{3}{10}  \\
      \amp = 3 + \frac{6}{10} +  \frac{6}{10} + \frac{3}{10} \\
      \amp = 3 + \frac{6+6+3}{10} \\
      \amp = 3 + \frac{15}{10} \\
      \amp = 3 + \frac{3}{2} \\
      \amp = 3 + 1 \frac{1}{2} \\
      \amp = {4{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Each page in this book is <m>{4{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> inches in height.</p>
</solution>
